  "text": "DisSent data is from [CITATION_1] , consisting of 4.7M sentences or clauses that were separated by a discourse marker from a list of 15 markers. Prediction of discourse markers based of the context clauses/sentences with which they occurred have been used as a training signal for sentence representation learning. Authors used handcrafted rules for each marker in order to ensure that the markers actually signal a form of relation. DisSent has underwhelming results on the GLUE tasks as a STILT [CITATION_2] .",
